@yanapeel is most comfortable in motion. After all, her work as the president of arts, culture, and heritage for @chanelofficial requires her to not only cross a dizzying number of latitudes and longitudes, but also traverse genres, overseeing the house's involvement in visula art and culture. One day you'll find her in conversation with @mistyonpointe at Davos; the next, speaking at the Aspen Ideas Festival with playwright @annadeaveresmith. In the mode of Gabrielle Chanel, who was friends with major artistic figures, she feels comfortable moving between worlds.
”[The] idea of art for all is really important to me,” she tells ELLE. To that end, she thinks of Chanel as “a house that can create time and space and extend the luxury of resources and long time horizons to artists, to institutions, and to the audiences they serve.”
Read the full interview with Peel at the link in bio.

